title: BrevisRefero and BioTalent
content: In September of 2021 I will be the faculty supervisor for a BioTalent Canada grant between BrevisRefero and Humber College.

title: BrevisRefero and Mitacs
content:
In September of 2020 I will be supervising a cluster of students from Humber College and Willis College through a six month Mitacs research project. Students will come from the Web Design and Interactive Media, User Experience, and Project Management programs from Humber College; and the Cyber Security Analyst from the Willis College.

In partnership with BrevisRefero students will contribute to the development and maintenance of their online RFP platform to connect BioPharma Innovator companies with a global network of Service Providers that offer biologics development and manufacturing services.

Mitacs helps connect industry and post-secondary institutions, driving collaborations to develop projects which solve business challenges, and develop Canadian innovation capacity.

title: Siemens Hackathon
content:
In February of 2020, a group of students from the Interactive Design Cluster at Humber College participated in a Siemens Hackathon during our Week 8: Playdays event.

In 2018 Humber College opened the Barrett Centre for Technology Innovation. This building is built to achieve LEED-Platinum certification and is a net-zero energy building. Students were provided with sample data from the building automation API and were given the task to visualize the data to help educate students about the building's features. The Siemens Hackathon was facilitated by faculty from Humber College and Siemens employees.

title: Humber News and the Canada Elections 2019
content:
In October of 2019 students from the Web Design and Interactive Media program from Humber College partnered with the students from the Humber News program during the 2019 federal election.

Students developed an interactive map using a custom build API, PHP, and jQuery; the interactive map was integrated with the existing Humber News WordPress website.

title: Toronto Elections 2018
content:
In October of 2018 students from the Web Design and Interactive Media program from Humber College partnered with the students from the Humber News program during the 2018 Toronto election.

Students developed an interactive map using live data from the Toronto elections API, Vue.js, Node.js, and Firebase; the interactive map was integrated with the existing Humber News WordPress website.
